# Internationalization

## Core Concepts

- See [Core Concepts](mdc:.cursor/rules/core.mdc) for project setup
- See [Client Layer](mdc:.cursor/rules/client.mdc) for UI integration
- See [API Layer](mdc:.cursor/rules/api.mdc) for server patterns
- Use react-i18next for translations
- Use i18next for translation management
- Support multiple languages
- Handle fallback languages

## Translation Structure

```typescript
// Translation types
type Translation = {
  common: {
    buttons: {
      submit: string;
      cancel: string;
    };
    errors: {
      required: string;
      invalid: string;
    };
  };
  features: {
    auth: {
      login: {
        title: string;
        description: string;
      };
    };
  };
};

// Usage in components
function LoginForm() {
  const { t } = useTranslation();
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>{t('features.auth.login.title')}</h1>
      <p>{t('features.auth.login.description')}</p>
    </div>
  );
}
```

## Translation Files

- Organize by feature
- Use nested structure for clarity
- Include type definitions
- Example:

  ```sh
  app/
    └── i18n/
        ├── en/
        │   ├── common.json
        │   └── features/
        │       └── auth.json
        └── es/
            ├── common.json
            └── features/
                └── auth.json
  ```

## Best Practices

- Use translation keys that match feature structure
- Include pluralization rules
- Handle number and date formatting
- Provide context for translators
